00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Pod 042 : Everything that lives is designed to end

4
00:23:25,024 --> 00:23:29,024
"They" are perpetually trapped ...

5
00:23:29,048 --> 00:23:32,448
... in a never-ending spiral of life and death.

6
00:23:33,472 --> 00:23:35,972
Is this a curse?

7
00:23:36,096 --> 00:23:38,596
Or some kind of punishment?

8
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:45,320
"They" often think about the god who blessed "them" with this cryptic puzzle ...

9
00:23:45,344 --> 00:23:48,344
... and wonder if they'll ever have the chance to kill him.

10
00:23:50,468 --> 00:23:54,468
2B: When I met him "that time",

11
00:23:54,492 --> 00:23:59,392
it was during our mission to destroy the Goliath-class weapon.

12
00:24:00,116 --> 00:24:01,916
9S: You're 2B, right?

13
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:08,440
My name's 9S. I'm here to provide support.

14
00:24:09,064 --> 00:24:12,664
2B: The No.9 Type S model is a high-end model.

15
00:24:12,688 --> 00:24:18,188
And it's because of that there's a constant danger of
them coming into contact with confidential information.

16
00:24:18,212 --> 00:24:24,912
That's why I've been tasked with the duty of eliminating him ...

17
00:24:25,736 --> 00:24:28,236
Over ... and over ...

18
00:24:30,460 --> 00:24:37,760
But ... The 9S of that time, he was somewhat different.

19
00:24:38,384 --> 00:24:43,784
9S: Scanners like me mostly work alone. Scouting out enemy lines and all that?

20
00:24:43,808 --> 00:24:49,808
So, I don't usually get a partner. It's kind of fun!

21
00:24:51,132 --> 00:24:55,732
2B: I simply ignored him when he'd speak.

22
00:24:55,856 --> 00:25:01,356
If I were to grow close to him, it'd only become more difficult to kill him.

23
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:07,280
