45
00:41:57,248 --> 00:42:00,948
However... I was a little uneasy about it.

46
00:42:01,572 --> 00:42:07,872
Scanner models like me usually work alone. And ...

47
00:42:07,896 --> 00:42:13,496
 I'd always gotten the impression that No.2 models were somewhat cold.

48
00:42:14,220 --> 00:42:23,420
So when she said those things to me in the hallway, I was ... kind of surprised.

49
00:42:24,044 --> 00:42:25,344
2B: 9S?

50
00:42:25,568 --> 00:42:26,768
9S: Yeah?

51
00:42:27,992 --> 00:42:29,492
2B: Thank you...

52
00:42:29,516 --> 00:42:34,816
For uploading my data to the Bunker.

53
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:40,640
9S: I’m sorry... I don’t have any memory of doing that.

54
00:42:40,764 --> 00:42:44,964
There wasn't a whole lot of bandwidth down there, you know?

55
00:42:44,988 --> 00:42:52,088
 I probably only had enough time to back up your memories.

56
00:42:53,112 --> 00:42:59,812
Mine are only intact up to the point just before we rendezvoused.

57
00:43:00,336 --> 00:43:02,336
2B: ... I see.

58
00:43:03,560 --> 00:43:09,660
9S: Things started out so awkward. At least, until that day ...

59
00:43:10,084 --> 00:43:14,584
