2B: ... 9S, don't you think you're overreacting?

72
00:43:57,796 --> 00:43:59,796
9S: Huh? Not you too, 2B!

73
00:44:00,020 --> 00:44:03,620
2B: Just leave it. The nano machines will heal it just fine on their own.

74
00:44:03,644 --> 00:44:05,644
9S: Er, I guess so ...

75
00:44:06,168 --> 00:44:09,968
Pod 042: Confirmation of mission completion by enemy annihilation.

76
00:44:09,992 --> 00:44:13,092
Recommendation: Report results to Command.

77
00:44:14,016 --> 00:44:16,316
9S: Um ... 2B?

78
00:44:16,940 --> 00:44:17,940
2B: What is it?

79
00:44:18,364 --> 00:44:21,764
9S: You think we could at least use the staunching gel?

80
00:44:21,788 --> 00:44:31,488
If contaminants enter the blood stream they'll be difficult to remove, and if it's just staunching
gel, then it shouldn't cause any problems to your motor functions, so, you know, just in case ...

81
00:44:31,512 --> 00:44:32,512
2B: ... All right.

82
00:44:32,536 --> 00:44:35,236
9S: Got it! Then I'll go ahead and prepare it right away!

83
00:44:35,260 --> 00:44:37,260
9S: Now where's that case ...

84
00:44:37,484 --> 00:44:38,684
2B: 9S.

85
00:44:38,708 --> 00:44:39,808
9S: Yeah?

86
00:44:41,232 --> 00:44:42,732
2B: ... Thank you.

87
00:44:45,156 --> 00:44:49,756
9S: I can't remember anymore what my response was when she said that.

88
00:44:50,380 --> 00:44:58,480
Just that I was so happy to be useful to someone.

89
00:44:59,204 --> 00:45:06,704
What was most important to me ... was being together with 2B.

90
00:45:07,828 --> 00:45:09,828
 ... At least.

91
00:45:12,052 --> 00:45:21,852
Until the day that YoRHa fell, along with the Bunker ...

92
